item.title: [SRL][RS2]PowerCutter
item.dc:creator: @sonny_bill_9 ``jason
item.description:
@sonny_bill_9 wrote:

hmm nashi i have a problem i log into runescape and the scar page stays up then when i lower it it checks the axe head and tells me the colours is there something wrong with the script
code is [code]{
CREDITS:
Secet - For his sexylicious FindBrokenAxe Function, I edited to suit this script
Weibs - I used his Antiban, I asked his permission for using it in another script
a while ago, so I presume it would still be alright. If not Pm me Weibs.
ronny.m.p - He helped me improve the main loop in my script
You - For using meh script
}

program PowerCutter;

procedure LogNewPlayer; forward;

{.include SRL\SRL.scar}
{.include SRL\SRL\skill\WoodCutting.scar}

//////////////////////////////////////////////////
/// SetUp Lines 46-40, 55, 59-62 && 83-87 ///
//////////////////////////////////////////////////

type
AUser = record
TreeToCut : String;
TreeC1 : Integer;
TreeC2 : Integer;
LogsToCut : Integer;
LogsChopped : Integer;
EXP : Integer;
end;

const
TreeCut = 0;
OakCut = 1;
WillowCut = 2;
MapleCut = 3;
YewCut = 4; //Dont stuff with these…
MagicCut = 5;
XPGained = 6;
LogDrop = 7;
LoadCut = 8;

var
Player : array of AUser;

const
StartPlayer = 0; //Player To Start With
MySRLID = ‘’; //Your Unique SRLID For SRL Stats (Leave Blank if you dont have one)
MySRLPassword = ‘’; //Your SRLID Password (Leave Black if you dont have a SRL Stats Account)
TheMouseSpeed = 0; //Your custom mousespeed, leave as 0 to make the mouse speed 1 + random(10)
SuperRandoms = False; //Set to true to do more random checks

procedure DeclarePlayers;
begin

HowManyPlayers := 1; // Set Number of Players here.
NumberOfPlayers(1);
CurrentPlayer := 0; // CurrentPlayer = Array Index

Players[0].Name := ‘bots 4 scar’; //Your Username
Players[0].Pass := ‘tester’; //Your Password
Players[0].Nick := ‘ots’; //3 or 4 letters from your Username
Players[0].Active := True; //Will You Be Using This Player?

Writeln(IntToStr(HowManyPlayers) + ’ Players’);

end;

////////////////////////
/// EXP GUIDE ///
///Tree = 25 ///
///Oak = 37 ///
///Willow = 62 ///
///Mahogany = 125 ///
///Yew = 175 ///
///Magic = 250 ///
////////////////////////

Procedure DeclarePlayerTree;
begin

SetArrayLength(Player, HowManyPlayers);

Player[0].TreeToCut := ‘tree’; //The Name of the Tree You Are Cutting
Player[0].TreeC1 := 2047319; //The Colour of the tree your are cutting
Player[0].TreeC2 := 1783374; //Another Colour of the tree your are cutting
Player[0].LogsToCut := 100; //How many logs For This User to cut
Player[0].EXP := 25; //See Guide Above For EXP

end;

{*******************************************************************************
function FindBrokenAxe: Boolean;
By: Secet
Description: Looks inventory for broken axe. Results true if found.
*******************************************************************************}
function FindBrokenAxe: Boolean;
var Broken,x,y: integer;
begin
Broken := DTMFromString(‘78DA6364676060606540011EF1990CFF81342’ +
‘310FF07024636208399010D302291409A9B48356C04D470020976’ +
‘22CCE126C21C1E026A40F670115003722F070135CC44AA6125A08’ +
‘695701802003CA406D8’);
GameTab(4);
if (FindDTM(Broken,x,y,553,204,744,463)) then
begin
WriteLn(‘Ent broke our axe =(’);
Result := True;
end else
FreeDTM(Broken);
end;

function FindAxeHeadColour: Boolean;
begin
GameTab(4);
wait(100 + random(200));
if ( ExistsItem ( 1 )) then
Mmouse(587, 219, 2, 2)
wait(200 + random(100));
if(IsUptext(‘Wield’))then
begin
HeadColor[0] := GetColor(590, 220);
HeadColor[1] := GetColor(587, 219);
HeadColor[2] := GetColor(588, 218);
Result:= true;
EquipAxe := False;
end;
If(Result = False)then
begin
GameTab(5);
wait(200 + random(200));
MMouse(592, 297, 2, 2);
wait(200 + random(100));
if(IsUptext(‘Remove’))then
begin
HeadColor[0] := GetColor(597, 294);
HeadColor[1] := GetColor(600, 295);
HeadColor[2] := GetColor(599, 298);
Result:= true;
EquipAxe := True;
end;
GameTab ( 4 );
end;
If(Result = true) then
begin
WriteLn(‘Axe head colors: ’ + IntToStr(HeadColor[0]) + ’ ’ + IntToStr(HeadColor[1]) + ’ ’ +
IntToStr(HeadColor[2]));
end else
begin
writeln(’’);
writeln(‘ERROR! cannot find axe in screen, please put axe in inventory or your equip page and restart the script!’);
writeln(’’);
end;
end;

function cBox2(X1, Y1, X2, Y2: Integer): TBox;
begin
Result.X1 := X1;
Result.X2 := X2;
Result.Y1 := Y1;
Result.Y2 := Y2;
end;

procedure LogIn;
begin

if (FindColor(x, y, 8353396, 262, 208, 262, 208)) then
begin
LogInPlayer;
end;

end;

procedure Report;
var
d: integer;
begin

if (not (Player[CurrentPlayer].LogsChopped >= Player[CurrentPlayer].LogsToCut)) then
begin
Writeln(’<===========================================>’);
Writeln(’ You Are Using Nashi’‘s PowerCutter’)
Writeln(’ Worked For ’ + TimeRunning);
for d := 0 to (HowManyPlayers-1) do
begin
if (Player[d].LogsChopped <> 0) then
begin
Writeln(’---------------------------------------------’);
Writeln(’ ’ + Players[d].Name + ’ Has…’);
Writeln(’ Cut & Dropped ’ + IntToStr(Player[d].LogsChopped) + ’ Logs!’);
Writeln(’ Gained ’ + IntToStr(Player[d].LogsChopped * Player[d].EXP) + ’ XP!’);
if (Players[d].Loc <> ‘’) then
Writeln(’ ’ + Players[d].Name + ‘’‘s Loc Is: ’ + Players[d].Loc);
end;
end;
Writeln(’<===========================================>’);
SRLRandomsReport;
end else
begin
Writeln(Players[CurrentPlayer].Name + ’ Has Finished Cutting…Changing Player’);
LogNewPlayer;
Exit;
end;

end;

procedure LogNewPlayer;
begin

LogOut;
Report;
NextPlayer(False);
FindAxeHeadColour;
NickNameBMP := CreateBitmapMaskFromText(Players[CurrentPlayer].Nick, UpChars);

end;

function NoAxe: Boolean;
var
c: Integer;
begin

c := CreateBitmapMaskFromText(‘You do not have an axe’, SmallChars);
if (FindBitmapMaskTolerance(c, x, y, 17, 410, 495, 452, 10, 85)) then
begin
Result:= True;
end else
begin
Result:= False;
end;

end;

function ChopTree(Colour1, Colour2: integer; TreeToCut: String): Boolean;
var
Attempts: Integer;
IgnoreBox: TBoxArray;
begin

MarkTime(Attempts);
Result:= False;
repeat
if FindColorSkipBoxArray(x, y, Colour1, MSX1, MSY1, MSX2, MSY2, IgnoreBox) then
begin
if FindColor(x, y, Colour2, x - 25, y - 25, x + 25, y + 25) then
begin
end;
MMouse(x, y, 5, 5);
GetMousePos(x, y);
wait(400);
FindEnt(Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeC1);
FindEnt(Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeC2);
if IsUpText('Chop down ’ + TreeToCut) then
begin
GetMousePos(x, y);
Mouse(x, y, 1, 1, true);
Result := True;
FindEnt(Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeC1);
FindEnt(Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeC2);
Wait(1000);
if not NoAxe then
Exit
else begin
Result := False;
Exit;
end;
end else
begin
GetMousePos(x, y);
SetArrayLength(IgnoreBox, GetArrayLength(IgnoreBox) + 1);
IgnoreBox[GetArrayLength(IgnoreBox) - 1] := cBox2(x - 25, y - 25, x + 25, y + 25);
LogIn;
case Random(11) of
0: begin
MakeComPass(‘N’);
SetArrayLength(IgnoreBox, 0);
end;
3: begin
MakeComPass(‘E’);
SetArrayLength(IgnoreBox, 0);
end;
7: begin
MakeComPass(‘W’);
SetArrayLength(IgnoreBox, 0);
end;
10: begin
MakeComPass(‘S’);
SetArrayLength(IgnoreBox, 0);
end;
end;
end;
end;
until((TimeFromMark(Attempts) > 300000));
if not (Result) then
begin
Players[CurrentPlayer].Loc:= ‘Unable To Find Tree’;
LogNewPlayer;
end;

end;

procedure FFight(CheckAxe: Boolean);
begin

if (CheckAxe) then
begin
if (FindBrokenAxe) then
begin
Players[CurrentPlayer].Loc := ‘Ent pwned your axe.’;
TypeSend(‘Dangit >_<’ + Chr(13));
LogNewPlayer;
end;
if (NoAxe) then
begin
Players[CurrentPlayer].Loc := ‘No Usable Axe’;
FindHead;
TypeSend(‘Argh…’ + Chr(13));
if not (ChopTree(Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeC1, Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeC2, Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeToCut)) then
LogNewPlayer
else
Players[CurrentPlayer].Loc := ‘’;
end;
end;

if (InBlack) then
begin
Players[CurrentPlayer].Loc := ‘In Black’;
LogNewPlayer;
end;

if (FindFight) then
begin
Writeln(‘Found Fight’);
RunTo(‘W’, True);
end;

if (FindDead) then
begin
Writeln(‘You Have Died…Changing Player’);
Players[CurrentPlayer].Loc:= ‘Died’;
LogNewPlayer;
end;

end;

procedure NantiBan;
begin
case 1 + Random(6) of
1 : BoredHuman;
2 : PickUpMouse;
3 : HoverSkill(‘random’, false);
4 : RandomMovement;
5 : RandomRClick;
6 : GameTab(1 + Random(13));
end;
end;

procedure NashiRandoms(CheckAxe, Nanti: Boolean);
begin
FindNormalRandoms;
FFight(CheckAxe);
if Nanti then
if Random(25) = 9 then
NantiBan;
end;

function DoneChop: boolean;
begin

if ((Player[CurrentPlayer].LogsChopped >= Player[CurrentPlayer].LogsToCut)) then
begin
Result:= True;
end else
begin
Result:= False;
end;

end;

procedure DropEm;
var
bmpLogMask, T: Integer;
begin

bmpLogMask := BitmapFromString(18, 14, ‘z78DA3330A015704302’ +
‘067404F4B471D4AEA162D7D0F5911B5E405D3369E15ADA85C3504’ +
‘F27F40400D1E72874’);
MMouse(584, 226, 5, 5);
Status(‘Dropping Logs’);
Gametab(4);
T := CountItemBmpMaskTol(bmpLogMask, 20, 25);
ReportVars[LogDrop] := ReportVars[LogDrop] + T;
case Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeToCut of
‘Tree’: ReportVars[TreeCut] := ReportVars[TreeCut] + T;
‘Oak’: ReportVars[OakCut] := ReportVars[OakCut] + T;
‘Willow’: ReportVars[WillowCut] := ReportVars[WillowCut] + T;
‘Maple’: ReportVars[MapleCut] := ReportVars[MapleCut] + T;
‘Yew’: ReportVars[YewCut] := ReportVars[YewCut] + T;
‘Magic’: ReportVars[MagicCut] := ReportVars[MagicCut] + T;
end;
ReportVars[XPGained] := ReportVars[XPGained] + (T * Player[CurrentPlayer].EXP);
Player[CurrentPlayer].LogsChopped := Player[CurrentPlayer].LogsChopped + T;
ClickAllItemsBmpMaskTolWait(‘rop’, bmpLogMask, 20, 25, 30+Random(30));

if (DoneChop) then
begin
LogNewPlayer;
Exit;
end;
Report;

end;

procedure CutItDown;
var
Waited4: Integer;
begin

while (not (InvFull)) do
begin
repeat
LogIn;
Status(‘Searching For Tree’);
until(ChopTree(Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeC1, Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeC2, Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeToCut));
Status(‘Cutting Tree’);
MarkTime(Waited4);
Wait(350);
NashiRandoms(True, False);
repeat
FindEnt(Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeC1);
FindEnt(Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeC2);
Report;
if SuperRandoms then NashiRandoms(True, True);
NashiRandoms(False, True);
LogIn;
Wait(300 + 100);
until ((IsUpText('Chop down ’ + Player[CurrentPlayer].TreeToCut) = False) or (TimeFromMark(Waited4) > 30000) or (InvFull));
end;
ReportVars[LoadCut] := ReportVars[LoadCut] + 1;
DropEm;
Wait(1000);

end;

begin

SetUpSRL;
ScriptID := ‘214’;
If MySRLID <> ‘’ then SRLID := MySRLID;
If MySRLPassword <> ‘’ then SRLPassword := MySRLPassword;
BenMouse := True;
if TheMouseSpeed = 0 then MouseSpeed := 1 + Random(10);
ClearDebug;
Writeln(‘Script Will Start In 3…’);
Wait(1000);
Writeln(‘Script Will Start In 2…’);
Wait(1000);
Writeln(‘Script Will Start In 1…’);
Wait(1000);
Writeln(‘Thank You For Using Nashi’‘s PowerChopper’);
Writeln(‘Hope You Dont Get Killed!’);
DeclarePlayers;
DeclarePlayerTree;
DisguiseScar(‘No page to display - Microsoft Internet Explorer’);
LogIn;
if not FindAxeHeadColour then
LogNewPlayer;
repeat
repeat
if not LoggedIn then NextPlayer(True);
CutItDown;
until (Player[CurrentPlayer].LogsToCut <= Player[CurrentPlayer].LogsChopped);
NextPlayer(false);
until (false);

end.[/code]and this is what it says in the dubug box

Script Will Start In 3... Script Will Start In 2... Script Will Start In 1... Thank You For Using Nashi's PowerChopper Hope You Dont Get Killed! 1 Players Axe head colors: 3818059 133197 65536 NextPlayer Found Compass

anyone help
thanks
~sonny bill 9~
